header:
E F M R trains are rerouted and experiencing extensive delays in both directions because of a network communications issue in Queens.

Some Jamaica-bound E F trains are running local from Queens Plaza and 21 St-Queensbridge to Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av.

Some Forest Hills-bound M trains will end at Myrtle Av, Delancey St-Essex St, or Chambers St on the J line and turn back around for Metropolitan Av-bound service.

Some Forest Hills-bound R trains will end at Court St and turn back around for Bay Ridge-bound service.

For alternative service, consider Q60 shuttle bus icon or see buses near you at bustime.mta.info.

Northbound R trains are rerouted in Manhattan and Queens because of a signal problem at Queens Plaza.

There is no northbound R service at 5 Av/59 St, Lexington Av/59 St or Queens Plaza. Northbound trains are running on the Q line from 57 St-7 Av to Lexington Av/63 St and then on the F line to 36 St (Queens), where they will resume making regular stops.

Expect extensive delays in N and W service in both directions. Expect delays in northbound Q and R service.

Alternatives

For service to 5 Av/59 St and Lexington Av/59 St, transfer to N and W trains at 57 St-7 Av. For service from those stations, take a southbound train to 57 St-7 Av and transfer to a rerouted northbound R train.

For service to/from Lexington Av/59 St, you can also walk between that station and Lexington Av/63 St, where rerouted northbound R trains are stopping. A free transfer will be available if you use your MetroCard.

For service to Queens Plaza, transfer to M trains at 34 St-Herald Sq. Or, take a northbound N or W train to nearby Queensboro Plaza. For service from Queens Plaza, take an M train.

R W trains are delayed and/or re-routed in both directions while we troubleshoot a malfunctioning switch north of Whitehall St-South Ferry.

Downtown R trains are running on the Q line from Canal St to DeKalb Av. For service to/from bypassed stations, take a W train.

Downtown W trains are running on the R line into Brooklyn, then turning around at 36 St.

Brooklyn-bound R trains are running on the Q line from Canal St to DeKalb Av.

That means you'll wait longer for an uptown local train in Manhattan. For service to Astoria, take an N train.

There are extensive delays in 2, 3, 4 and 5 train service in both directions while our crews investigate a signal problem at President St.

To reduce congestion in Brooklyn:
-Some southbound 4 and 5 trains will end at Bowling Green.
-Some southbound 2 and 3 trains will end at Chambers St or Rector St on the 1 line.

For alternate service in Manhattan and Brooklyn, consider taking N, Q and R trains. Transfer points include:
-Times Sq - 42 St 2/3/N/Q/R
-59 St 4/5/N/R
-Atlantic Av - Barclays Ctr 2/3/4/5/N/Q/R

Some southbound 5 trains are running via the 2 line from 149 St-Grand Concourse to Nevins St.
Expect delays on southbound 4/5 trains.

Jamaica-bound E F and Forest Hills-bound M R trains are delayed and/or rerouted because of a switch problem near 75 Av.

Jamaica-bound E F trains are running on the local track from Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av to Forest Hills-71 Av.

Some Queens-bound trains will end in Manhattan to reduce congestion:
Some Jamaica-bound E trains will run on the C line from 50 St to 168 St, the last stop.
Some Forest Hills-bound R trains will run on the Q line from 57 St-7 Av to 96 St, the last stop.
Northbound B C Q trains may experience delays while they share the tracks with rerouted trains.

B D Q service is disrupted while we move a train with a mechanical problem off of the Manhattan Bridge.

B Trains
In Brooklyn, northbound trains are only running from Brighton Beach to Prospect Park, the last stop.

Any trains that have passed Prospect Park will run on the N line from Canal St to Times Sq-42 St, the last stop.

D Trains
Northbound trains that depart from Coney Island-Stillwell Av are running on the F line from to Broadway-Lafayette St.

Trains that are in Brooklyn and have already departed will run on the N line from DeKalb Av to 57 St-7 Av and then on the Q line to 96 St, the last stop.

Q Trains
Some northbound trains are running on the N line from Coney Island-Stillwell Av to DeKalb Av.

The following BxM7 buses will not run today -
Bronx-bound 4:48pm.
Manhattan-bound 6:30pm. 
Check for updates before traveling.

There is no southbound R service at Queens Plaza, Lexington Av/59 St or 5 Av/59 St while we investigate what activated a train's brakes near Queens Plaza.

Southbound R trains are running on the F line from 36 St to Lexington Av/63 St and then on the Q line to 57 St-7 Av.

Expect longer waits for southbound R trains.

There is no northbound F service at 57 St, Lexington Av/63 St, Roosevelt Island, or 21 St-Queensbridge while we investigate what activated a train's brakes at Lexington Av/63 St.

Northbound F trains are running on the M line from 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr to Queens Plaza and then on the E line to Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av.

Expect delays in northbound service.

If your stop is skipped, take a southbound train.

Alternatives
For service to 57 St, take rerouted F trains to 5 Av/53 St or take Q trains to 57 St-7 Av. For service from this station, take a southbound train to 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr and transfer to a northbound train.

For service to Lexington Av/63 St, take Q trains by transferring at 34 St-Herald Sq. For service from this station, take a southbound train to 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr and transfer to a northbound train.

For service to Roosevelt Island, take a northbound Q train to Lexington Av/63 St and transfer to the Roosevelt Island Tram with your MetroCard. For service from that station, take a southbound train to 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr and transfer to a northbound train.

For service to/from 21 St-Queensbridge, use nearby Queens Plaza where E M and rerouted F service is available.

There is a partial suspension in 4 and 5  trains service while EMS provides medical assistance for someone at Brooklyn Bridge-City Hall.
Southbound 4 trains end at Brooklyn Bridge-City Hall and turn for northbound service.
Southbound 5 trains are running on the 2 line from 149 St-Grand Concourse to Nevins St.
Northbound 4 and 5 trains are ending at Wall St and turn for southbound service.
Expect delays in 2, 3, 4 and 5 service in both directions.
For travel between Manhattan and Brooklyn, consider taking 2, 3, A, C, and R trains.

There are delays and multiple impacts to A B C D train service while we investigate what caused a temporary loss of third rail power near 96 St.

There are no trains running between 145 St and 59 St-Columbus Circle in both directions. 

A C trains
The last stop on some northbound trains will be Howard Beach-JFK Airport, Euclid Av, Broadway Junction, Chambers St or 59 St-Columbus Circle.
The last stop on southbound A and C trains will be 145 St.

B trains
B trains are suspended out of Bedford Park Blvd. Take the D instead. 
The last stop on northbound B trains will be Prospect Park.

D trains
The last stop on some northbound trains will be 34 St-Herald Sq or W 4 St-Wash Sq
Some northbound D trains are running on the Q line from Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr to 96 St.

Alternatives
Take the 1 2 3 trains making nearby station stops.

J M trains are delayed and/or rerouted because of a switch malfunction at Myrtle Av.

There is limited J service between Manhattan and Brooklyn. 

There is no M service between Manhattan and Brooklyn in either direction.

Jamaica-bound J trains will end at Delancey St-Essex St.

Some Broad St-bound J trains will end at Broadway Junction.

Metropolitan Av-bound M trains will end at 2 Av on the F line and return in service towards 71 Av.

Travel Alternatives:

See a station agent to receive a courtesy pass for continuing train or bus service.
For Brooklyn and Queens-bound service from Delancey St-Essex St, consider taking a Coney Island-bound F train and transferring between the A C G L for continuing service in Brooklyn or Queens.
For service between Myrtle Av and Marcy Av, consider taking the nearby B46 bus. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2uV4BKj
For service between Myrtle-Wyckoff Avs and Myrtle Av, consider taking the nearby B54 bus. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2LrRNVO
For service between Fresh Pond Rd and Myrtle-Wyckoff Avs, consider taking nearby Q58 or B13 buses. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2mPlzFy
For local service between Kosciuszko St and Marcy Av, consider taking the nearby B46 bus. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2Ope0lh
For local service between Kosciuszko St and Jamaica Center-Parsons/Archer, consider taking the nearby Q24 bus. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2OnnFsD

We’re investigating an incident in which an uptown A train came into contact with debris on the tracks at 14 St.

A Trains
Service is suspended between Jay St-MetroTech and 59 St-Columbus Circle.

All Manhattan-bound trains will turn around at Jay St-MetroTech for Queens-bound service.

All downtown trains will end at 59 St-Columbus Circle, then turn around for uptown service.

C Trains
Service is suspended in Manhattan and Brooklyn.

D Trains
Service is suspended between W 4 St-Wash Sq and 59 St-Columbus Circle.

Northbound D trains will end at either Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr or W 4 St-Wash Sq, then turn around for Coney Island-bound service.

Southbound D trains will end at 59 St-Columbus Circle, then turn around for Bronx-bound service.

E Trains
Service is running between Delancey St-Essex St and Jamaica-Van Wyck, via the Sixth Avenue line in Manhattan, for this weekend’s planned work.

However, expect severe delays on the E line in both directions.

F Trains
Service is running between Church Av and Jamaica-179 St, via Sixth Avenue in Manhattan.

Some F trains are running on the G line between 36 St and Bergen St.

Alternatives

Use the 2 and 3 trains to/from Brooklyn, the 1, 2 and 3,  4 and 6, and N and Q in Manhattan, and the 7 line to/from Queens.

There is limited B Q service between Manhattan and Brooklyn in both directions while our crews make repairs to a rail Prospect Park.

Some southbound B trains will end at 2 Av on the F line and return northbound for service. 

Some southbound Q trains will end at Times Sq-42 St. 

Some southbound Q trains are stopping along the N line from DeKalb Av to Coney Island-Stillwell Av.

There are delays and reroutes to N R W service in both directions while our crews remove debris from the tracks in the 60th St Tunnel.

There is no northbound R service at 5 Av/59 St, Lexington Av/59 St or Queensboro Plaza. Northbound R trains are running on the Q line from 57 St-7 Av to Lexington Av/63 St and then on the F line to 36 St.

There is no northbound N service between Times Sq-42 St and Astoria-Ditmars Blvd.
The last stop on northbound N trains will be Times Sq-42 St.
The last stop on northbound W trains will be 96 St on the Q line.

For service between Manhattan and Queens, take an E F M or 7 train.

There is no Forest Hills-bound M service from 5 Av/53 St to Queens Plaza because of a switch problem at 5 Av/53 St.

Forest Hills-bound M trains are running on the F line from 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr to 36 St.

E trains have resumed making regular stops.

Expect delays in E F M service.

Alternatives
For Forest Hills-bound M service to those stations:
Transfer to northbound 6 trains at Broadway-Lafayette St and take them to 51 St where E is available.
Transfer to 42 St Shuttle trains at 42 St-Bryant Pk and take them to 6 for northbound 6 trains to 51 St.
For Forest Hills-bound service from those stations, take E service to Queens Plaza, where R service is available making all M stops.

Southbound N trains are running express from Kings Hwy to Coney Island - Stillwell Av while we investigate what activated a train's brakes at Avenue U.

If your stop is skipped, take a northbound N train. Or, transfer to a southbound D train at New Utrecht Av and exit at a nearby station.

2 and 5 trains are delayed and/or rerouted in both directions while EMS responds to someone who was struck by a train at 3 Av-149 St.
There is no 2 service between Prospect Av and 135 St.
There no 5 service between Prospect Av and 149 St-Grand Concourse.
Northbound 2 trains will end at 137 St-City College on the 1 line or at Harlem-148 St on the 3 line.
The last stop for southbound 2 trains in the Bronx will be Prospect Av or E 180 St.
5 trains are running on the 4 line between 149 St-Grand Concourse and Bowling Green.
As alternative, customers can take nearby 4, 6 and D trains and crosstown Bx6, Bx15, Bx17, Bx19, Bx21, Bx33, Bx36 and Bx40 bus service.

Northbound N R trains are delayed and/or rerouted while our crews replace rails at Cortlandt St.
Northbound N trains are running on the Q line from DeKalb Av to Canal St.
Northbound R trains will end at Court St and turn around for southbound service.
For service to/from bypassed stations, take a southbound train.

There is no southbound service on the B and D lines past Broadway-Lafayette St while we work to move a work train with a mechanical problem on the Manhattan Bridge.

Southbound B trains are running on the F line from Broadway-Lafayette St to 2 Av, the last stop.

Southbound D trains are running on the F line from Broadway-Lafayette St to either 2 Av or Coney Island - Stillwell Av, the last stop.

Some southbound N trains are running on the D line from 36 St to Coney Island - Stillwell Av to provide service at affected stations. Listen for train announcements at 36 St to determine where your train will go.

Expect delays on B, D, F and M trains in both directions.

ALTERNATIVES - Manhattan

For alternate service in Manhattan, consider transferring to A/C service at 59 St - Columbus Circle, or E service at 7 Av, and using nearby stations along 8 Av. 

ALTERNATIVES - Manhattan into Brooklyn 

For service from Manhattan into Brooklyn, take N/Q/R service. Transfer between trains at 34 St - Herald Sq in Manhattan or travel to nearby stations.  You can also take rerouted D trains to 4 Av - 9 St on the F line and transfer to a southbound R train at that station. 

ALTERNATIVES - Brooklyn - B Train

Take Q trains.

ALTERNATIVES - Brooklyn - D Train

For D service, take southbound N trains for alternate service between Atlantic Av - Barclays Ctr and 36 St. 

For service between 36 St and Coney Island - Stillwell Av, take N trains rerouted onto the D line or use nearby N stations. You can also transfer from southbound N trains to northbound D trains at New Utrecht Av/62 St or Coney Island - Stillwell Av.

Also, consider taking these crosstown buses from D stations to nearby stations:
-50 St : Take B11 buses to/from Avenue I on the F line or 45 St on the N line.
-55 St : Take B16 buses to/from Fort Hamilton Pkwy on the N line or Church Av on the F line.
-18 Av, 20 Av, Bay Pkwy and 25 Av : Take B1 buses to/from 86 St on the N line.

Coney Island-bound F trains are rerouted while emergency teams respond to someone who was struck by a train at 57 St.

Some Coney Island-bound F trains are running on the E line from Jackson Hts - Roosevelt Av to 5 Av/53 St, then on the M line to W 4 St - Wash Sq.

The remaining Coney Island-bound F trains are running on the E line from Jackson Hts - Roosevelt Av to Queens Plaza and then on the G line to Bergen St.

There is no Coney Island-bound F service at 57 St.

Expect extensive delays in F service in both directions.

The last stop on northbound 4/5/6 trains is 86 St.
Last stop on southbound 4 is 149 St.
Southbound 5 running via 2 from 149 St to Chambers St.

There are delays and multiple impacts to N Q R service while we investigate what activated a train's brakes near City Hall.

N Trains
Northbound trains are holding in stations in Lower Manhattan.

Some southbound trains will end early and turn back to provide northbound service.

Q R Trains
Northbound Q R trains are running on the D line from DeKalb Av to 34 St-Herald Sq and then on the F line to Lexington Av/63 St.

Note: Northbound R trains will continue on the F line to 36 St (Queens).

Some southbound trains will end early and turn back to provide northbound service.

Alternatives
For service between Brooklyn and Manhattan, take 4 5 trains from Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr or Borough Hall or A trains from Jay St-MetroTech.

There are delays and/or reroutes in 4 , 5 and 6 service while emergency teams respond to a person who was struck by a train at Grand Central-42 St.

There is no 4 5 6 train service between Brooklyn Bridge-City Hall and 86 St in both directions.

Some southbound 4 trains will end at 86 St or 149 St-Grand Concourse and return northbound for service. 

5 trains are stopping along the 2 line between Nevins St to 149 St-Grand Concourse in both directions.

Some southbound 5 trains will end at E 180 St and return northbound for service.

Some southbound 6 trains will end at 86 St or 3 Av-138 St and return northbound for service.

We’re investigating an incident in which an uptown A train came into contact with debris on the tracks at 14 St.

A Trains
Service is suspended between Jay St-MetroTech and 59 St-Columbus Circle.

All Manhattan-bound trains will turn around at Jay St-MetroTech for Queens-bound service.

All downtown trains will end at 59 St-Columbus Circle, then turn around for uptown service.

C Trains
Service is suspended between 59 St-Columbus Circle and Euclid Av.

Trains are running between 59 St-Columbus Circle and 207 St on the A line to provide alternate service.

D Trains
Service is suspended between W 4 St-Wash Sq and 59 St-Columbus Circle.

Northbound D trains will end at either Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr or W 4 St-Wash Sq, then turn around for Coney Island-bound service.

Southbound D trains will end at 59 St-Columbus Circle, then turn around for Bronx-bound service.

E Trains
Service is running between Delancey St-Essex St and Jamaica-Van Wyck, via the Sixth Avenue line in Manhattan, for this weekend’s planned work.

However, expect severe delays on the E line in both directions.

There is no service at 5 Av/53 St or Lexington Av/53 St in either direction.

There is no service to/from Manhattan on the E train platform at Court Sq. Trains that stop at that platform will run on the G line to/from Brooklyn and experience extensive delays.

If you're in Queens, take the 7 or go to Queensboro Plaza and take the N.

F Trains
Service is running between Church Av and Jamaica-179 St, via Sixth Avenue in Manhattan.

Some F trains are running on the G line between 36 St and Bergen St.

R Trains
R trains have resumed their regular route between Bay Ridge-95 St and Forest Hills-71 Av. For service to/from Queens, consider taking a 7 train, if possible.

Alternatives

Use the 2 and 3 trains to/from Brooklyn, the 1, 2 and 3, 4 and 6, and N and Q in Manhattan, and the 7 line to/from Queens.

We’ve set up a temporary bus shuttle from Jay St-MetroTech to Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr. If you’re trying to get to Manhattan, we recommend taking a 2/3 or N/Q train at Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr.

There are major delays and multiple impacts to Q service in both directions while our crews repair third rail that was damaged by a fallen tree near Avenue H :

There is no northbound Q service at stations from Avenue M to 7 Av.

Most northbound Q trains are running on the N line from Coney Island-Stillwell Av to Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr.

Some northbound Q trains will run on the Q line but only until Kings Hwy, the last stop.

Brooklyn Alternatives
Between Coney Island-Stillwell Av and Church Av, consider taking nearby B68 buses on Coney Island Ave (which connect to F service at Church Av) or F trains.

Between Avenue H and Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr, take nearby 2 trains.

Here are some station-specific alternatives

For service to/from Prospect Park, consider taking the Franklin Av Shuttle, or transferring between the nearby B12 bus and 2 service at Winthrop St. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2mHIkLp

For service to/from Church Av, consider transferring between the nearby B35 bus and F G service at Church Av & McDonald Av: http://bit.ly/2AhryMy Or 2 service at Church Av & Nostrand Av: http://bit.ly/2NM277M

For service to/from Newkirk Plaza, consider transferring between the nearby B8 bus and 2 service at Newkirk Av. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2NL8AQi

For service to/from Avenue J, consider transferring between the nearby B6 or B11 buses and 2 service at Flatbush Av. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2JVNnRw

Manhattan Alternatives
Between Canal St and 57 St-7 Av, take N R trains.

For Lexington Av/63 St, take F trains by transferring at 34 St-Herald Sq. Or use nearby Lexington Av/59 St (N R).

For 72 St, 86 St and 96 St, take nearby 6 trains. Transfer at 14 St-Union Sq or Lexington Av/59 St (N R).

Northbound 2 trains have resumed making regular stops from Nevins St to 149 St-Grand Concourse while NYPD investigates after someone was struck by a train at 125 St.

3 service is still suspended between 96 St and Harlem-148 St in both directions. Northbound 3 trains are running on the 1 line from 96 St to 137 St-City College, the last stop.

Southbound 2 trains are running on the 5 line from 149 St-Grand Concourse to Nevins St.

Expect major delays in both directions.

Alternatives
Take southbound 4 5 or rerouted 2 trains to stations on the east side of Manhattan. Use crosstown buses to get to/from the west side of Manhattan such as the M14A/D-SBS, M34-SBS, M34A-SBS, M66, M72, M79-SBS, M86-SBS, M96, M116, M60-SBS, M100, M101, Bx15 and Bx19. Also, transfer to 42 St Shuttle trains at Grand Central-42 St and L trains at 14 St-Union Sq.

E, F, M and R trains are delayed and re-routed because someone was struck by a train at Grand Av-Newtown.

Some northbound E and F trains are running on the local track from Queens Plaza/21 St-Queensbridge to Forest Hills-71 Av.

There is no M train service between Delancey St-Essex St and Forest Hills-71 Av in either direction.

71 Av-bound M trains will end at Chambers St on the J line and turn around for service to Middle Village-Metropolitan Av.

Some northbound R trains will end at 57 St-7 Av.

Some northbound R trains are stopping along Q line from 57 St-7 Av and will end at 96 St.

Manhattan-bound R trains are running on the express track from Forest Hills-71 Av to Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av.

For alternate service along Queens Blvd, take a Q60 bus.  See buses near you at bustime.mta.info

Southbound E F and M trains are delayed and rerouted while we address a signal problem at 36 St.

Southbound E and F trains are running on the local track from Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av to Queens Plaza.

Some rerouted F trains will run along the G line from Queens Plaza to Bergen St.
Some rerouted F trains will run along the E line from Queens Plaza to 5 Av/53 St, then along the M line to 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr.

M trains are not running between Forest Hills-71 Av and Delancey St-Essex St in both directions.

Northbound 1  trains are ending at 137 St-City College and return for southbound service while emergency teams respond to someone who was struck by a train at Dyckman St.
There is no northbound 1  train service between 137 St-City College and Van Cortlandt Park-242 St.
For service north of 137 St-City College, consider using the A train, Bx7 and Bx9 buses.

There are delays and reroutes in A and C trains while FDNY responds to a track fire near 14 St.
Southbound A and C trains will run on the D line from 59 St-Columbus Circle to Broadway-Lafayette St and end at 2 Av on the F and turn back around for northbound service.
Northbound A and C trains will end at Jay St-MetroTech and turn back around for southbound service.
Some northbound F trains are running on the G line from Bergen St to Court Sq-23 St.
Expect extensive delays in A, C  and F  service in both directions.
As an alternative, consider taking 1 or D trains.

There is no northbound 6 service from Manhattan into the Bronx while we work to fix a signal problem that activated a train's brakes near 125 St.

Northbound 6 trains are ending at 86 St or 125 St. Some southbound 6 trains will end at 3 Av-138 St and turn back to provide northbound service.

Some northbound 5 trains are running on the 2 line from Nevins St to 149 St-Grand Concourse to reduce congestion.

Expect delays in northbound 4 5 and in 6 service in both directions.

Alternatives
Take Bx15 buses from 125 St to Brook Av, where Bronx-bound 6 trains are available.

There are delays and multiple impacts to 2 3 4 5 service while emergency teams respond to a person who was struck by a train at 116 St.

2 Trains
There is no service from the Bronx to the west side of Manhattan. Southbound trains are running on the 4 line from 149 St-Grand Concourse to Nevins St.

3 Trains
Service is suspended between 96 St and Harlem-148 St in both directions.

Northbound 3 trains are running on the 1 line from 96 St to 137 St-City College, the last stop.

4 Trains
Expect delays in southbound service.

5 Trains
Trains are only running between E 180 St and Eastchester-Dyre Av. Service is suspended Manhattan and the rest of the Bronx.

Jamaica-bound E and 71 Av-bound M trains are delayed and/or rerouted while we investigate why a train's brakes were activated near Queens Plaza. 

E trains are stopping along the F line from W 4 St-Wash Sq to Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av.

Some northbound F trains are stopping along the G line from Bergen St to Court Sq-23 St then via the E line to Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av.

M trains are stopping along the F line from 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr to 36 St in Queens.

F M trains are delayed and/or rerouted while our maintenance teams troubleshoot a signal malfunction near W 4 St-Wash Sq.
Some Coney Island-bound F and Metropolitan Av-bound M trains are running on the express track from 34 St-Herald Sq to W 4 St-Wash Sq 
If your stop is skipped, take a Queens-bound train.
To ease congestion on the 6th Ave line, some Coney Island-bound F trains are rerouted on the E line from Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av to Queens Plaza then on the G line to Bergen St.  
Expect longer waits for B D E G R trains while sharing the tracks with rerouted trains.

Q train service is part-suspended and rerouted while emergency teams respond to someone who was struck by a train at Ocean Pkwy.

There is no Q service between Kings Hwy and Coney Island-Stillwell Av in both directions.

Northbound Q trains are running on the N line from Coney Island-Stillwell Av to Atlantic Av-Barclays Ctr.

For service to/from bypassed stations, consider using southbound Q service, or visiting a station agent to request a free courtesy pass for local bus service to nearby F or N stations.

Expect extensive delays to N and Q  service in both directions.

Southbound N Q R W trains are running with severe delays.
Southbound trains have resumed making regular stops in Manhattan.
Expect northbound delays.

Brooklyn-bound 5 trains via 2 from 149 St (GC) to Nevins St. 
Last stop on Brooklyn-bound 4/5 is Brooklyn Bridge.
Last stop on some uptown 4 is Wall St.

Northbound A C trains are running on the F line from Jay St-MetroTech to W 4 St-Wash Sq while we troubleshoot a work train with a mechanical problem near Jay St-MetroTech.

Expect delays on northbound F trains while they share the tracks.

Alternatives
High St: See a station agent for a courtesy pass for continuing train or bus service.  Consider taking the nearby 2 3 lines at Clark St. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2GL1uHH 
Fulton St : Take northbound J trains to Delancey St-Essex St, where rerouted A C service is available on the F platform.
Canal St : See a station agent for a courtesy pass for continuing train or bus service. Consider taking the nearby 1 line at Canal St on Varick St for service uptown. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2IIHUhb 
Spring St: See a station agent for a courtesy pass for continuing train or bus service.  Consider taking the nearby 1 line at Houston St for service uptown. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2x9c9wi

F trains are running on the C line in both directions between W 4 St-Wash Sq and Jay St-MetroTech while FDNY responds to a report of smoke at York St.

There is no F service at Broadway-Lafayette St, 2 Av, Delancey St-Essex St, East Broadway or York St.

Some F trains may run on the G line between Bergen St and Court Sq and on the E line between Court Sq and Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av to reduce congestion.

Expect delays on A, C and F trains in both directions.

Alternatives
Broadway-Lafayette St - For uptown service, take M trains. For service to Brooklyn, take an uptown B, D or M train to W 4 St-Wash Sq, where rerouted F service is available.
2 Av - Take nearby B or D trains at Grand St or B, D and M trains at Broadway-Lafayette St.
Delancey St-Essex St - For uptown service, take M trains. For service to Brooklyn, take a downtown J train to Fulton St, where rerouted F service is available on the C line platform.
East Broadway - Travel to nearby Delancey St-Essex St for M service.
York St - Travel to nearby High St for rerouted F service.

Southbound F trains are rerouted from Queens into Manhattan while NYPD responds to people being disruptive on a train at 21 St-Queensbridge.

There is no southbound F service at 21 St-Queensbridge, Roosevelt Island, Lexington Av/63 St or 57 St.

Southbound F trains are running on the E line from Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av to 5 Av/53 St and then on the M line to 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr.

Expect delays on southbound E, F and M trains.

Some southbound F trains may run on the G line from Court Sq to Bergen St, bypassing Manhattan, to reduce congestion.

Southbound Alternatives

For southbound service to/from 21 St-Queensbridge, take a northbound F train.

For service from Roosevelt Island, take the Roosevelt Island Tram. For service to that station, take a northbound F train to Jackson Hts-Roosevelt Av.

For service from Lexington Av/63 St, take a southbound Q train and transfer to F trains at 34 St-Herald Sq. For service from that station, transfer to a northbound F train at 47-50 Sts-Rockefeller Ctr.
